        <mxCell id="wtadDzqarJSNFot-p4i7-29" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="10" width="10" x="1180" y="672.25" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wtadDzqarJSNFot-p4i7-30" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;autosize=1;resizable=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;Most of the control logic is decentralized.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Instruction aligner sees which one&#39;s of the 2 instructions is valid.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Consumed is 0 in case of stall, 1 for 1 alid instruction and 2 for two valid ones.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Use a fetch buffer.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Use valid for instructions too. In case of invalid ones, do not allocate an entry to ROB.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Simple predictor and target address give precedence to older instruction, if both are valid branch instructions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Red signals do not go through pipeline registers.&lt;/div&gt;Dispatch will decide whether to send an instruction to an alternative issue buffer or stall the prior pipeline.&lt;div&gt;For jump type instructions, issue buffer will send op1 = pc and op2 = 4.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 51, 51);&quot;&gt;Single register file. Copies shown just to make the diagram convenient.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;Register file has 8 read ports and 4 write ports.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;br_taken generated by each respective ALU issue buffer.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;After passing through write-back arbiter, if there was a conflict, old instructions tag is set to 0.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="600" x="764.5" y="65" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="6ow7Os2RDueyfXFCd-y1-1" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=none;dashed=1;html=1;rounded=0;" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1240" y="903" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="1240" y="320" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
